column5: This moon is found atop the back right side of the castle roof, climb the small spire to grab the moon

column5: This moon can be activated on the bottom side of the central plaza by throwing cappy at the glowing Top Hat on the top of the arch

column4: Nice Shot with the Chain Chomp!

column4: Very Nice Shot with the Chain Chomp!

column4: A Tourist in the Cascade Kingdom
column5: This moon is acquired by talking to the tourist who can be found near the taxi north of the odyssey (in its revisit location)

This moon is acquired by talking to peach on the top side of the kingdom right by the exit of the 8-bit section
This moon is the first koopa freerunning moon
This moon is the second koopa freerunning mood
This moon can be bought at the shop on the bottom north side of the kingdom
This moon can be acquired by capturing the binoculars on the very south side of the kingdom, then zooming in and looking at the sphynx
This moon can be activated by groundpounding the glowing spot under water underneath the bridge in the centre of the kingdom

column4: Just a Hat, Skip, and a Jump
column5: This moon can be found on the far east side of the back  section of the kingdom and requires you to activate some floating clouds to reach

This moon can be found next to the bridge at the very top of the kingdom, look along the front side and you should see it floating over the edge
This moon can be activated by holding cappy on the horn of the dinosaur skull at the top of the kingdom near the waterfall

This moon requires you to capture the dinosaur, then immidiately turn to your right and break the blocks directly next to the dinosaur. Then move the dino out of the way and groundpound the glowing spot to activate the moon

This moon is found at the top of the kingdom near the electrical wire/peach. Capture the chain chomp closest to the fossils near the waterfall, aim the chomp at the fossil near the electrical wire and when lined up properly, release to break open the fossil
This moon is acquired by catching the bunny which can be found near the shop
This moon is acquired by entering the 2d section at the back of the kingdom, activating the music notes and collecting them all
This moon is the second koopa freerunning moon
This moon can be found in the moon pipe towards the back side of the kingdom. This moon is acquired by making your way to the end of the subarea and collecting it

column4: Atop a Wall Among the Clouds
column5: This moon can be found in the moon pipe towards the back side of the kingdom. This moon can be found on top of the first wall along the left side of the subarea

This moon can be found in the moon pipe around the centre of the kingdom, where the odyssey is first found in the beginning of the game. This moon can be acquired by making your way to the end of the subarea and collecting it

column4: Flying Far Away from Gusty Bridges
column5: This moon can be found in the moon pipe around the centre of the kingdom, where the odyssey is first found in the beginning of the game. This moon can be acquired by making your way to the left side of the subarea, throwing cappy into the boost at the right time to grab the lever at the end of the whirlwinds
This moon is one of Sand Kingdom's story moons, found at the top of the 2d tower in the centre of the kingdom
This moon is one of Sand Kingdom's story moons, found on the west island. Go around and collect all the shards to spawn the moon
This moon is one of Sand Kingdom's story moons, given to you after the hariet boss fight at the top of the inverted pyramid
This moon is one of Sand Kingdom's story moons, given to you after the Knucklotec boss fight at the end of the hole where the inverted pyramid use to be
This moon can be found in the town near the beginning of the kingdom. It can be found at the top of one of the buildings near the last electrical pole
This moon can be found in the ruin area in the middle of the kingdom. Underneath where the bullet bill spawns is a little alcove area where you will find this moon
This moon can be found on a small pillar east of the ruins area just before the poison lake

column4: Hidden Room in the Flowing Sands
column5: This moon can be found in the most northern part of the quicksand portion of the ruins. Look along the west wall and you should see a segment that is raised above the sand. Sink just below this line while moving towards it, then start jumping once you're under it. You will then be in a small hidden room with the moon

This moon can be found in the 2d tower in the centre of the kingdom. Make your way to the top of the 2d section but just before jumping up and out of the 2d section, head directly left instead to find a secret area where you will find the moon

This moon is the secret moon in the 2d section of the inverted pyramid that goes around the outside. Just before you head through the final pipe, continue heading left where you will find a secret area and the moon

column4: On Top of the Stone Archway
column5: This  moon can be found on top of the archway that acts as the entrance to the ruins area. You can reach the top by either exiting out of the electrical wire, jumping off one of the ice pillars towards the side or making your way over with the bullet bill

column4: From a Crate in the Ruins
column5: This moon can be activated by breaking open the glowing crate next to the bullet bill spawner in the centre of the ruins
This moon is found on the lone pillar on the east side of the kingdom and can be reached by either a bullet bill or by grabbing glydon at the top of the kingdom
This moon can be activated by throwing cappy at the tail of one of the statues on top of the inverted period, on the north west side

column4: Hang Your Hat on the Fountain
column5: This moon can be activated by throwing cappy at the top of the water foundain in the centre of the town near the beginning of the kingdom
This moon can be activated by groundpounding the mound of sand on the eastern side of the little oasis area found to the east of the town near the beginning of the kingdom
This moon can be activated by groundpounding the top of the big hill found north west of the town near the beginning of the kingdom.
This moon can be activated by groundpounding the glowing spot of the ground found near a bunch of luggage to the east of and near the inverted pyramid

This moon can be acquired by capturing a bullet bill in the lower south east part of the ruins, then heading east you will find a hole in the wall. Head through the hole and break open the cage to grab the moon

column4: Inside a Block Is a Hard Place
column5: This moon can be acquired by capturing a bullet bill in the lower south east part of the ruins, then bringing it over and crashing it into the glowing block in the bottom south east corner of the ruins
